digraph {
    label=NOTES

    1 [shape=plaintext, label="
(1) If the machine is \"controlled by hardware\", it means
that the control has been taken from the software
by the hardware; it could happen e.g. when there was
a power outage, or simply there is any problem detected
by the hardware.

(2) \"Logging-in\" involves two-factor authentication.

(3) Every notification for the maintainers includes
the machine's serial number and the reason it has been sent
for.

(4) \"Starting the paying\" means particularly
that the user either insert the cash, use the card, or use
any other available way of starting the paying.

(5) \"Ending the paying\" means particularly
that either the user is inserting the last lacking amount
of cash, or the paying is being completed in any other way
that is required by the paying method that was used.

(5a) \"Paying\" does not involve split payments.

(6) \"Predicting the level of an ingredient\"
during the \"ingredients check\" means predicting the level
of this ingredient after the product that this ingredient
is to be used to prepare is eventually prepared.

(7) As a \"problem\" during the \"ingredients check\"
it is considered, among others, an invalid arrangement
of ingredients in particular containers, and an invalid
arrangement of containers themselves.

(8) As a \"problem\" during \"cleaning\" it is considered,
among others, that the sewage container is full.

(9) As a \"problem\" during \"initializing\"
it is considered, among others, that the machine
has not been yet configured initially.

(10) \"General configuration\" allows configuring
all of the settings of the machine other than products
and payments.

(11) \"Configuring products\" allows configuring
the number of products.

(11a) \"Configuring products\" allows configuring
recipes.

(11b) \"Configuring ingredients\" allows configuring
the number of containers.

(12) \"Configuring payments\" allows setting either none,
one, or several payment methods.

(13) It is assumed that one ingredient is stored
in one and only one container, and that one container
is storing one and only one ingredient.
    "]
}
